## Complete Arabic (RTL) Localization & Internationalization Implementation

Implement a complete production-grade Arabic localization system for the entire Tyre Pulse application. This is not just text translation. The application must behave like a native Arabic enterprise application used across Saudi Arabia, UAE, Qatar, Kuwait, Bahrain, Oman, and other Arabic-speaking countries.

### Internationalization (i18n)

* Audit every page, component, dialog, modal, form, table, chart, notification, email template, PDF report, and exported document.
* Remove all hardcoded English text.
* Store every visible string in localization files.
* Support dynamic language switching without requiring users to log out.
* Remember the user's preferred language.
* Default language should be selected based on the user's country or browser language on first login.

### Right-to-Left (RTL) Layout

Implement full RTL support across the entire application.

When Arabic is selected:

* Entire application switches to RTL.
* Sidebar moves to the right.
* Navigation drawers open from the right.
* Menus align correctly.
* Dialogs respect RTL.
* Cards align naturally.
* Forms mirror correctly.
* Tables support RTL reading.
* Charts keep numeric values readable while respecting RTL layouts.
* Timeline components reverse direction where appropriate.
* Breadcrumbs reverse correctly.
* Stepper components flow right-to-left.
* Icons that indicate direction (back, next, expand, collapse, arrows) automatically mirror where appropriate.
* Pagination controls reverse correctly.
* Carousels and onboarding slides work naturally in RTL.

### Typography

Use fonts optimized for Arabic.

Examples:

* IBM Plex Sans Arabic
* Cairo
* Tajawal
* Noto Sans Arabic

Define typography separately for Arabic and English.

Adjust:

